nodes.documentation:
The Ownable constructor sets the original `owner` of the contract to the sender
account.
Throws if called by any account other than the owner.
nodes.name: onlyOwner

nodes.documentation:
Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.
 newOwner The address to transfer ownership to.
nodes.name: transferOwnership

nodes.documentation: @return true if `msg.sender` is the owner of the contract.
nodes.name: isOwner

nodes.documentation:
Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.
 Renouncing to ownership will leave the contract without an owner.
It will not be possible to call the functions with the `onlyOwner`
modifier anymore.
nodes.name: renounceOwnership

nodes.documentation:
Transfers control of the contract to a newOwner.
 newOwner The address to transfer ownership to.

methods.constructor: The Ownable constructor sets the original `owner` of the contract to the sender account.

renounceOwnership().notice: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract. Renouncing to ownership will leave the contract without an owner. It will not be possible to call the functions with the `onlyOwner` modifier anymore.
